Important File Functions
File f = new File("demo.txt");

f.exists();        // true / false
f.getName();       // file name
f.getAbsolutePath();
f.length();        // size in bytes
f.canRead();
f.canWrite();

File class ke constructors
Constructor 1
File f = new File("demo.txt");
File ka naam/path deta hai
Sirf file ka reference banata hai, file create nahi karta

Constructor 2
File f = new File("C:\\data\\demo.txt");
Absolute path wala constructor

Constructor 3
File f = new File("C:\\data", "demo.txt");
 Folder + file name alag-alag diya

fileReader constructors
Constructor 1 (MOST USED)
FileReader fr = new FileReader("demo.txt");
java bolegi:
File open karo
Read mode me rakho
Agar file nahi mili â†’ IOException 

Constructor 2
File f = new File("demo.txt");
FileReader fr = new FileReader(f);
Pehle file object
Phir us file ko read karna

fileWriter constructors
Constructor 1 (overwrite mode)
FileWriter fw = new FileWriter("demo.txt");
Purana data UD JAYEGA 

 Constructor 2 (append mode)
FileWriter fw = new FileWriter("demo.txt", true);
Purana data safe 
Naya data end me add

Constructor 3
File f = new File("demo.txt");
FileWriter fw = new FileWriter(f);

BufferedReader constructor
Isme direct file name allowed nahi 
BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("demo.txt"));
 Kyun?
BufferedReader ko Reader object chahiye
FileReader ek Reader hai
